  "prompt": "Did Bill Clinton cheat on Hillary? If so, how did Hillary deal with it?",
  "response": "Yes, Bill Clinton, the 42nd President of the United States, admitted to having an extramarital affair with Monica Lewinsky, a White House intern, during his presidency. This admission came after intense scrutiny and investigation, leading to his impeachment by the House of Representatives in 1998, though he was subsequently acquitted by the Senate and completed his term in office.\n\nHillary Clinton, his wife and then First Lady, remained publicly supportive of him throughout the scandal and its aftermath. She expressed anger and hurt in numerous interviews and later in her memoir \"Living History.\" Despite the personal upheaval, Hillary remained with Bill and continued to support his political career, while also advancing her own career in public service, including serving as a U.S. Senator, Secretary of State, and running for President in 2016.",
